<span id="freeTextContainer12619976388733554110">The first several novels in the Anita Blake series are great. Funny, scary, a touch gory and a touch sexy. As you read each book, you can really see the character development as Anita becomes more sure of herself and more comfortable with the &quot;monsters&quot;. However, some the later books have deteriorated into little more than soft porn for women. Not that there&apos;s anything wrong with that. <br/><br/>However, I feel it cheapens the series, which features a great role model in Anita as a women who has accepted </span>
  <span id="freeText12619976388733554110" style="display:none">The first several novels in the Anita Blake series are great. Funny, scary, a touch gory and a touch sexy. As you read each book, you can really see the character development as Anita becomes more sure of herself and more comfortable with the "monsters". However, some the later books have deteriorated into little more than soft porn for women. Not that there's anything wrong with that. <br /><br />However, I feel it cheapens the series, which features a great role model in Anita as a women who has accepted that her life works the way it is and makes her happy, even it is not what the rest of the world thinks is normal. She is strong, independent, and accepting of her sexuality. </span>
